org.cesecore.audit.enums

Enum ModuleTypes

  • java.lang.Object
    • java.lang.Enum<ModuleTypes>
      • org.cesecore.audit.enums.ModuleTypes
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.io.Serializable, java.lang.Comparable<ModuleTypes>, org.cesecore.audit.enums.ConstantType<org.cesecore.audit.enums.ModuleType>, org.cesecore.audit.enums.ModuleType

    public enum ModuleTypes
extends java.lang.Enum<ModuleTypes>
implements org.cesecore.audit.enums.ModuleType
    When doing secure audit log it is necessary to identify from which module a security audit event originates. A modules is a group of related functionality. This class contains the modules in the CESeCore core itself.
    See Also:
    EventTypes, ServiceTypes
